<!DOCTYPE assessment PUBLIC "-//Carnegie Mellon University//DTD Inline Assessment MathML 1.4//EN" "http://oli.cmu.edu/dtd/oli_inline_assessment_mathml_1_4.dtd"><assessment xmlns:cmd="http://oli.web.cmu.edu/content/metadata/2.1/" id="hair_growth_digt"><title>tutor</title><page><question id="q1"><body>Which of the following stages of hair growth is correctly matched to its description?</body><multiple_choice select="single" shuffle="true"><choice value="A">anagen — growth phase after telogen</choice><choice value="B">catagen — resting phase after telogen</choice><choice value="C">telogen — degenerative phase before anagen</choice></multiple_choice><part id="bd888ce88a0b4c188cf8ac31c8c715c2"><skillref idref="hair_growth_SKILL" /><response match="A" score="10"><feedback>Correct. Anagen is the growth phase before catagen and after telogen.</feedback></response><response match="B" score="0"><feedback>Incorrect. Catagen is the transition phase between anagen and telogen.</feedback></response><response match="C" score="0"><feedback>Incorrect. Telogen does precede anagen, but it is not a stage where things are degenerating.</feedback></response></part></question></page></assessment>
